gomodel:SYNGO_3662  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Transverse hippocampal slices (400 micromolar) were submerged and continuously superfused with Krebs. Synaptic transmission was elicited and field EPSPs (excitatory post synaptic potentials) were recorded with 1- to 3-Mohm\npipettes filled with 3 M NaCI.\n\nSynaptic strength was monitored as maximal slope of the field EPSP recorded in hippocampal area CA1 during 0.033-Hz stimulation of the Schaffer collateral and commisural pathways.\n\nFigs 1A, B show the contribution of Cav2.2 (N-type) to synaptic vesicle exocytosis by demonstrating that a specific blocker of N-type channels (omega-Conotoxin-GVIA) causes a rapid (but incomplete) depression of synaptic transmission.\n\n16/5/2017 Pim\n- N-type calcium channels are typified by the CACNA1B subunit.. Experimental description: Transverse hippocampal slices were obtained from 3- to 4-week old Sprague-Dawley rats" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3662" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

